  "body": "- [X] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nI couldn't find any documentation about how to unsubscribe from an event once you have subscribed to it with TruffleContract 4.0.x., neither in [the Github README here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/tree/develop/packages/truffle-contract), nor on [Truffle's website](https://truffleframework.com/docs/truffle/reference/contract-abstractions)\r\n\r\nIn Truffle Contract 4.0.2, how do you unsubscribe from an event once you subscribed to it?\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst eventEmitter = contractInstance\r\n                .MyEvent({ fromBlock: '0' })\r\n                .on(\"data\", function(event) {\r\n                    //do something with event\r\n                })\r\n                .on(\"error\", function(error) {\r\n                    // do something with error\r\n                });\r\n```\r\n\r\neventEmitter.unsubscribe and eventEmitter.off are both undefined.\r\nThe only option that worked was eventEmitter.removeAllListeners(), but as @gnidan said, that's the nuclear option.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache 2.0.2\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.2\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 10.15.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.4.1\r\n* truffle-contract version: 4.0.2\r\n",
